To calculate the Return on Assets (ROA), the formula is:

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Total Assets}} \times 100\%
\]

Given data:

- Net Profit = 143,922.03
- Total Assets at beginning (2023-12-31) = 16,000,000.00
- Total Assets at end (2024-02-04) = 19,520,226.07

Step 1: Calculate Average Total Assets

\[
\text{Average Total Assets} = \frac{16,000,000.00 + 19,520,226.07}{2} = \frac{35,520,226.07}{2} = 17,760,113.04
\]

Step 2: Calculate ROA

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{143,922.03}{17,760,113.04} \times 100\% = 0.0081 \times 100\% = 0.81\%
\]

Therefore, the ROA is approximately 0.81%.
